sentences: Eric Paul Mandat (born 1957) is an American clarinetist and composer.
In a November 2005 review of Sean Osborn's album American Spirit, Fanfare magazine remarked that Mandat's music creates "amazing technical effects for the instrument" that are "startling and eerie."

He has performed in the Chicago Symphony Orchestra's MusicNOW Series (including as principal clarinet for Pierre Boulez's 80th Birthday Concert under Boulez's baton and a performance of Osvaldo Golijov's Ayre with Dawn Upshaw).
In a review in The Clarinet of Mandat's Folk Songs, the author found that "A composition of this caliber will most likely enter the performance repertoire as the representative piece of the decade!"
